programme.desc: Laura is a former construction worker who spent years exposed to the harsh elements. Our whole team of experts has kicked into gear to turn back the clock and transform this former construction worker from hard hat to hottie.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: I'm No Grandma
programme.desc: Kathy is a mother who has battled health setbacks while raising her kids. She wants to shake off her general malaise and look better as a first step to feeling better. Find out how Kathy goes from dreary to cheery in her journey to look ten years younger.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Self Conscious To Self Confident
programme.desc: Laura, a public speaker, has lost her self-confidence and is now only self-conscious. Once upbeat and bubbly, she suffered from an illness that took its toll on her appearance and self esteem. Can our experts help Laura regain her identity and a new look?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Jilly Graham
programme.desc: Nicky Hambleton-Jones and her team of age-busting experts come to the rescue of Jilly Graham from Bradford.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Soccer Mom to Soccer Bomb!
programme.desc: Colleen Radcliffe is a mother of four and says she doesn't have a spare second to spend on herself. Colleen feels like the old mom with no end in sight, but we're here to teach her that isn't the case. Time to make Colleen look 10 Years Younger!

programme.title: Wild At Heart
programme.desc: After the devastating loss of Leopard's Den, the family are split across continents. Caroline, Liv and a heavily pregnant Alice are in the UK, while Danny and Du Plessis have remained in South Africa.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 2
programme.desc: Danny returns to South Africa with Caroline, Liv and Charlotte. They are all excited to be back and are looking forward to seeing their new home, Clearwater Farm.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: Danny has been preparing his pitch for an Endangered Species Project. JLW, a pharmaceutical company, are looking to fund an environmental project and the family hope that this grant money will enable them to buy Leopard's Den and Mara.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: Danny and Ed release two cheetah brothers together, a symbol of their new partnership, but not all of the family are happy about this new start. Caroline is still furious at what she sees as Danny's betrayal of Du Plessis.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5
programme.desc: The family are still estranged following Caroline's decision to move back to the decrepit Clearwater house with Du Plessis. Rosie is determined to reunite everyone, and plans a civilised dinner as a step towards reconciliation.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 6
programme.desc: Danny is in prison, accused of murdering Peeters, but Du Plessis is determined to prove his friend's innocence by any means he can. Du Plessis' first attempt backfires disastrously when he harangues a police officer and ends up in a cell next to Danny.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 7
programme.desc: With Danny away, and Du Plessis undertaking an ignominious stretch of community service, Ed is left in charge of running the Endangered Species Project.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 8
programme.desc: Danny and Ed are anxiously preparing for a review with JLW, the pharmaceutical company that fund their Endangered Species Project. They are desperate for it to go smoothly, and as a result are driving the rest of the family mad.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 9
programme.desc: Retired construction worker, Ivan, has come to the Embassy with a major financial problem. He purchased a luxury condo in Phuket two years ago, but he still hasn't received the ownership papers from the developer. And it's not looking good.

programme.title: Big Families: Can't Stop, Won't Stop
programme.desc: We meet three families who are either expecting or planning a baby at the same time as seeing their older children, grow up, move out and start their own families.

programme.title: Big Families: Sibling Rivalry
programme.desc: Our first family have 10 children between the ages of a few months and their early teens. With all of the children so close in age, all of the kids are still at a stage where they desperately need their parents love and attention.

programme.title: Big Families: Price and Prejudice
programme.desc: Our first family are determined not to take government handouts. Dad works, mum stays at home and does the odd job and they budget to stay afloat. In their opinion, it was their choice to have 12 children so it's their responsibility to look after them.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 10
programme.desc: Mark came to Bali 18 months ago to setup an I.T. business with his Indonesian wife. But unbeknownst to Mark, his passport contains a fake immigration stamp that was issued by a fake immigration agent.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 1
programme.desc: Thailand is in a state of political unrest and 41-year-old David, a musician from New South Wales, has just been arrested for overstaying his visa. Can the embassy get him out?

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 2
programme.desc: The embassy is called to a young couple in crisis. Their 7 month-old baby girl, Laney, has died from a virus and they need to get her home to Australia. But can they get baby Laney on the plane?

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 3
programme.desc: The embassy is on high alert after a wealthy Australian banker goes missing. Is he alive? Holed up in a bar somewhere? Or does he not want to be found?

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 12
programme.desc: The chopper team is called out to save a motorbike racer who's crashed at 200ks per hour and a woman scalded by an exploding radiator, plus an elderly golfer in a kilt suffers a heart attack on the 18th hole.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 13
programme.desc: A 39 year old man has crashed his bike 15 kilometres south of Auckland city and an elderly man has collapsed while walking. He is unable to speak properly and is incorreherent at Waiheke Island.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 1
programme.desc: The Rescue 1 chopper team struggle to save a Paeroa farmer.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 2
programme.desc: Tropical rain has hit Wellsford, flooding the entire town and leaving a pregnant woman and her unborn child fighting for their lives.

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Oldest Car Manufacturers
programme.desc: It’s time to get nostalgic: who do you think is the most important pioneer of the automotive world? We do a little time travel and trace back the trail of the modern car.

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Greatest Car Legends
programme.desc: Some cars are not just a means of transport, but influenced entire generations and became legends on their own. That’s why we won’t talk about expensive, fast or successful cars on this episode.

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Ugliest Cars
programme.desc: The car-manufacturers' design departments are constantly tinkering around, in a quest to invent the perfect car. And more often than not, very elegantly-shaped cars are the result.

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Most Beautiful Cars
programme.desc: Today we are going for Lux. It has been said that beauty is in the eye of the beholder. So we promise to maintain some objectivity. Desirable cars are what we want, and what we shall get.

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Rarest Automobiles
programme.desc: Most manufacturers sell their models in other countries. The production figures, therefore, easily rise into the hundreds of thousands.

programme.title: Top Ten Show: The Best Sport Versions of Small Cars
programme.desc: Almost every compact car is now available in a sporty version. And funnily enough the little racers usually have more power under the bonnet than you might think.
programme.sub-title: The Best Sport Versions of Small Cars

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 01
programme.desc: An angry bull, a few English people prepared for the weather and a young, talented race driver - tourists will be venturing down to the infamous 'green hell' of the Nürburgring!

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 02
programme.desc: A tuned-up Golf 2, a family sedan from Hannover, Germany and a very special Porsche GT2! We will be looking behind the scenes of the gas station by the curve on the race track where sports cars flock!

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 03
programme.desc: The Nürburgring has transformed into a winter wonderland, but although it looks pretty it sure is not pretty to use it as a race track.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 04
programme.desc: Fog, rain and snow means that a visit to the Eifel region is not that pleasant right now. Nevertheless, the hardcore drivers are out of the track and are not letting the weather get in their way.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 05
programme.desc: The Nürburgring. Here you can really let your hair down on a spectacular and difficult race track and learn how to get fit for motor sports. That is why motor fans come here to the Nürburgring throughout the year!

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 06
programme.desc: On today's episode, we will be treating you to some very entertaining clips from the Nürburgring. Expect to see the pedal on the metal and rubber burning up the place!

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 07
programme.desc: The weather has cleared up a bit on the Nürburgring and we are finally back on the track. As soon as the snow and ice has gone the horsepower junkies return to the ring to tear it up once again.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 08
programme.desc: On today's show we will be showing you the history of a racing legend who has won the 24-hour race four times in a row: Olaf Manthey. Stick around and perhaps you will find out the secret of his success.

programme.sub-title: Beauty is More Than Skin Deep

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Polishing the Prize

programme.sub-title: The Homecoming Queen Gets Her Crown Back

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 8

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 08
programme.desc: On today's show we will be showing you the history of a racing legend who has won the 24-hour race four times in a row: Olaf Manthey. Stick around and perhaps you will find out the secret of his success.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 09
programme.desc: Christian Menzel has asked presenter Miriam to participate in some driver safety training! He will be showing you tips and tricks on what to do in emergency situations.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 10
programme.desc: Spring has finally melted away the snow on the track and life on the Nürburgring is starting to flourish once again. It is full of drivers with gasoline in their hearts and cars that roar around the ring.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 11
programme.desc: It is time once again for the VLN Endurance Racing Championship! While the drivers are already out there doing test laps, we will be taking you behind the scenes and showing what really goes on in the pit lanes.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 12
programme.desc: Great cars and pretty girls. The Nürburgring is shaking as the VLN begins its second leg of the tournament. We will be commentating on this exciting competition, as well as showing highlights of the BMW's 1st leg win.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 13
programme.desc: The fourth race of the VLN season is regarded as a dress rehearsal for the 24 hour race. For the top teams and best drivers this is the last opportunity for a real hard test.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 14
programme.desc: Today, we are going to look back at the highlight of last week. The 24 hour race - as always it was exciting. In addition 'Strong Man Run' and a look at the tourist drivers.

programme.title: Track Masters
programme.desc: Some heavy guns are going to be driven around the ring on today's show. We are at the Truck Grand Prix and shall be following the progress of driver Uwe Nittle as he gets ready for qualifying.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 16
programme.desc: On today's show, we will be taking a look at the RCN Challenge - the BMW Driving Experience. Also on the show, we will be paying a visit to the Devils Diner - the indoor meeting place for drivers on the ring!

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 17
programme.desc: Now that the 24-hour race is over we have left the Nürburgring and moved to Büren, Germany, where Räder Sport is based. Famous for really fast front-wheel drives, it provides a lot of horsepower down on the track.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 18
programme.desc: The roaring sounds of engines and exhausts usually dominate the Nürburgring but on today's episode, we're focusing on something a little quieter. Ever fancied a 15-mile bike ride around the ring, or perhaps a 16-mile run?

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 19
programme.desc: On today's episode, we are going old-timer crazy, like the Mercedes S for example with 160 horsepower that lead Rudolf Caracciola to victory in the 1927 opening race. Do not to miss this old-timer grand prix event!

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 20
programme.desc: Phoenix Racing, the successful team from the Eifel Region rocks the DTM. We will be showing you some pit stop training with the Swiss rookie Rahel Frey, a Ford GT kit car and a tuned Honda with a Spaniard at the wheel!

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 21
programme.desc: Today on the Nürburgring: Patrick is tearing up the track in an Aston Martin Zagato with 12 cylinders of pure sound! Also on the show: a hummer, a Bremer Clio and a Frenchman in a Ferrari!
